## End-State Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TB
  subgraph asterisk ["Asterisk (zero Go — YAML only)"]
    subgraph manifest ["origami.yaml"]
      m_schematics["schematics: rca, knowledge"]
      m_connectors["connectors: rp, github, docs"]
      m_assets["domain_serve: circuits, prompts,\nschemas, scorecards, reports"]
    end
    circuits["circuits/*.yaml"]
    scenarios["scenarios/*.yaml"]
    scorecards["scorecards/*.yaml"]
    prompts["prompts/*.md"]
    vocab["vocabulary.yaml"]
  end
  subgraph origami ["Origami (Go engine + collections)"]
    engine["framework (walk, DSL, vars, templates)"]
    fold["origami fold (YAML → unified binary)"]
    resolver["binding resolver (sockets → connectors)"]
    codegen["codegen (wired binary template)"]
    subgraph schematics ["schematics/"]
      rcaSch["rca/ (MCP server, F0-F6 circuit)"]
      knowSch["knowledge/ (git + docs access)"]
    end
    subgraph connectors ["connectors/"]
      rpConn["rp/ (ReportPortal I/O)"]
      ghConn["github/ (git driver)"]
      docsConn["docs/ (docs driver)"]
    end
    transformers["transformers (http, jq, file, match, dedup)"]
  end
  manifest -->|"origami fold"| fold
  fold --> resolver --> codegen
  codegen -->|"generates"| binary["bin/asterisk\n(unified: domain + MCP + connectors)"]
  m_schematics --> rcaSch
  m_schematics --> knowSch
  m_connectors --> rpConn
  m_connectors --> ghConn
  m_connectors --> docsConn
  circuits --> engine
  scenarios --> engine
  transformers --> engine
```

